      "id": "bug-004",
      "timestamp": "2026-06-26T06:20:00.000Z",
      "error_message": "new row violates RLS / Failed to create team (500) — team_members insert FK fails because public.users profile row is missing",
      "file": "src/app/api/auth/register/route.ts",
      "root_cause": "Register inserted the public.users profile via the user-scoped supabase client. Right after signUp() in a server route the session isn't set on that client, so auth.uid() is null and the users_own RLS policy (auth.uid() = id) blocks the insert. profileError then deleted the auth user. Net result: accounts exist in auth.users with no public.users profile row, so any later team_members insert (FK -> public.users) fails.",
      "fix": "Insert the profile via the admin (service-role) client instead of supabase, matching how teams/route.ts inserts team_members. Existing broken accounts created before the fix must be re-registered or have their public.users row backfilled.",
      "tags": [
        "supabase",
        "rls",
